It's that faith, that faith of the woman with the issue of blood that just knew that there was healing in the wings of God Almighty and reaches out and touches the one, the only one, the only one that can actually cleanse me of this thing

01:02:09.762 --> 01:02:14.108
The physical element, Lord, just a picture of the spiritual one.

01:02:14.989 --> 01:02:18.174
God, we thank you for what you've done for us.

01:02:18.314 --> 01:02:19.356
We thank you for the cross.

01:02:19.396 --> 01:02:22.881
We thank you for your body broken for us.

01:02:24.083 --> 01:02:25.925
In Jesus' name, we take the bread together.

01:02:34.477 --> 01:02:34.898
The blood.

01:02:44.642 --> 01:02:48.006
Jesus, this cup we hold in our hands.

01:02:51.952 --> 01:02:53.453
We recognize now what it cost.

01:02:55.436 --> 01:03:05.289
We recognize now that you said, Father, if there's any other way, not my will but yours.

01:03:06.811 --> 01:03:07.552
This is your will.

01:03:11.016 --> 01:03:12.338
Lord, to experience.

01:03:14.082 --> 01:03:14.683
The pain.

01:03:17.286 --> 01:03:19.108
The pain that you did on our behalf.

01:03:20.570 --> 01:03:26.197
God, we're so grateful for this blood that we recognize.

01:03:26.258 --> 01:03:37.472
It's culturally counterintuitive that something as able to stain as blood could wash us clean, but it does.

01:03:38.233 --> 01:03:42.258
Would you turn our death into life?

01:03:44.226 --> 01:03:44.987
Lord, you cleanse us.

01:03:45.107 --> 01:03:48.472
Why does snow?

01:03:48.492 --> 01:03:50.294
It might look rough on the outside.

01:03:50.354 --> 01:04:00.247
That's the beautiful thing is that it looks like death on the outside, but you never really cared about the outside.

01:04:02.110 --> 01:04:11.222
Lord, it is the cleansing, the spiritual cleansing of your blood in our lives that brings us near to you, that allows us to be in your presence.

01:04:12.364 --> 01:04:14.066
So we take the cup

01:04:14.210 --> 01:04:15.792
together in Jesus' name.

01:04:20.159 --> 01:04:24.746
Lord, as we sing this last song, would it not just be words?

01:04:24.966 --> 01:04:27.751
Would it not just be us doing something to do it?

01:04:27.971 --> 01:04:40.049
God, it would be an outpouring of our hearts, the posture of our hearts to glorify you, to worship you, not to put on a pedestal all that we've done for you, but to simply acknowledge all you've done for us.

01:04:40.149 --> 01:04:42.533
We are so grateful in the mighty name of Jesus.

01:04:42.733 --> 01:04:43.154
Amen.
